      "edited_at": "2025-09-17T09:15:25.895Z",
      "content": "<p>Image dissection underpins RootImage= in unit files, systemd-nspawn&#39;s --image= switch or systemd-gpt-auto-generator, the various --image= switches of tools such as systemd-tmpfiles, systemd-sysusers and so on, and is also what systemd-mountfsd wraps for unprivileged clients.</p><p>The dissection logic is quite powerful, it can enforce security policies on what it is doing there and can unlock images with LUKS or Verity. </p><p>With systemd v258 there&#39;s one more place where image dissection is used:</p>",
      "reblog": null,
