      "replies_count": 1,
      "reblogs_count": 0,
      "favourites_count": 7,
      "quotes_count": 0,
      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p>There&#39;s now a &quot;dissect_image&quot; built-in in udev. (&quot;built-ins&quot; in udev are little programs that udev can invoke on a device via udev rules, that are linked directly into the udev binary, i.e. are not implemented via external call-out binaries). </p><p>The new builtin is automatically invoked on the root disk booted into via a new udev rules file (90-image-dissect.rules). The results are used to generate a bunch of symlinks to the right partition block devices in the /dev/disk/by-designator/\u2026 subdir.</p>",
      "reblog": null,
